\section{Pinched and bumped nanotube}

The shape of the transmittance vs energy for pinched and bumped nanotubes seem to be very similar, but the potential wells are deeper in the pinched case. 
To make the shift to lower energy in the pinched case clearer we plot in Fig. \ref{fig5} the transmittance as function of incident energy for both the bumped and pinched nanotubes for $\epsilon =0.95$. 

